# Check before cross-impact changes

Before implementing, **stop and ask the user** when a change could affect behavior outside the stated request.

## High-risk areas in this project (always ask first)

- `script.js`: schedule load/save/sync — `loadAllSchedules`, `mergeRemoteSchedulesAfterLoad`, `performSave`, `saveAllSchedules`, polling, `initTeachers`, student/teacher calendar merge
- `functions/api/schedules.js`, `functions/api/roster.js`, `functions/lib/roster-scope.js`, `functions/lib/kv-safe.js`
- Auth/session: login restore, Bearer token, `loggedInStudentFullName` / teacher isolation
- Anything that writes to Cloudflare KV on page load (not only on explicit user action)

## What to send the user before editing

1. **What** you plan to change (files + behavior)
2. **What else** it might affect (roles, devices, refresh, cross-browser)
3. **Smallest fix** vs broader option

Wait for explicit approval before editing when blast radius is more than one isolated UI tweak.

## Proceed without asking only when

- Change is clearly isolated (e.g. one CSS rule, one label, one button the user named)
- User already approved that exact scope in the same thread
- User said "go ahead" after an impact summary

## Implementation discipline

- One concern per change set; no stacking heal/merge/sync layers in one pass
- Prefer the smallest diff that fixes the approved issue only
- Do not redesign calendar, sidebar, colors, or unrelated features unless asked
